## Ubiquitous Computing

<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="150" align="left" style="padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px" />

A breakthrough in quantum computing has been achieved with a prototype processor exhibiting an impressive 99.9% qubit fidelity. This advancement is not just a milestone, but a beacon of hope for the future of technology. It addresses one of the field's significant challengesreducing errors in quantum calculations. Researchers believe that maintaining such high fidelity could accelerate the development of practical quantum computers, paving the way for their application in various industries.  [Read More](https://www.livescience.com/technology/computing/prototype-quantum-processor-boasts-record-99-9-qubit-fidelity)

<hr>

<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="150" align="left" style="padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px" />

MIT researchers are moving closer to creating quantum computers capable of code-breaking abilities. Their work focuses on developing algorithms that exploit the unique properties of quantum systems, potentially disrupting traditional encryption methods. As these technologies evolve, the cybersecurity landscape will face significant challenges, prompting a swift response from those relying on classic encryption.  [Read More](https://news.mit.edu/2024/toward-code-breaking-quantum-computer-0823)

<hr>



IBM highlights the double-edged sword of quantum computers in cybersecurity. While they promise to enhance data processing speeds, they pose a significant risk to existing encryption protocols. As quantum technology capabilities improve, it becomes increasingly vital for industries to urgently adopt quantum-safe encryption methods to safeguard sensitive data. The ongoing arms race between quantum development and data security continues to unfold, and the time to act is now.  [Read More](https://uk.finance.yahoo.com/news/quantum-computers-encryption-expose-data-ibm-050014920.html)

## Cybersecurity

<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="150" align="left" style="padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px" />

Hong Kong is set to implement its first critical infrastructure cybersecurity law to fortify defenses across essential sectors. The legislation will require organizations to enhance their cybersecurity measures and report incidents, reflecting a growing commitment to addressing vulnerabilities in technology and infrastructure. This law is a significant step towards a more secure digital future, underscoring the importance of proactive security measures in safeguarding critical services from rising cyber threats. [Read More](https://www.globalcompliancenews.com/2024/09/03/hong-kong-the-first-critical-infrastructure-cybersecurity-law-is-on-the-horizon/)

<hr>

<img src="data:image/webp;base64," width="150" align="left" style="padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px" />

A former engineer in Missouri has been charged with compromising secure systems to steal sensitive data, raising alarms about insider threats within the cybersecurity landscape. These charges underscore a significant trend where trusted employees may exploit their access to systems for personal gain. Law enforcement officials emphasize the necessity of vigilant monitoring and oversight of internal personnel to mitigate these risks, as even seemingly reliable employees can become potential vulnerabilities in an organization's security framework. [Read More](https://thehackernews.com/2024/09/ex-engineer-charged-in-missouri-for.html)

<hr>

<img src="data:image/webp;base64," width="150" align="left" style="padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px" />

The RansomHub ransomware group has successfully breached an alarming 210 organizations, raising significant concerns within cybersecurity communities. This incident underscores the group's advanced techniques in extortion and emphasizes the critical need for comprehensive incident response planning. Cybersecurity experts urge all organizations to bolster their defenses and develop robust strategies to combat potential breaches. As cyber threats become increasingly prevalent and sophisticated, enhancing resilience against such attacks should be a top priority for all businesses in today's digital landscape. [Read More](https://thehackernews.com/2024/09/ransomhub-ransomware-group-targets-210.html)

## Artificial Intelligence

<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="150" align="left" style="padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px" />

A recent NPR article discusses how Donald Trump utilizes artificial intelligence to create memes and deepfakes, specifically in his campaign strategy. He aims to engage younger voters and adapt to evolving digital landscapes by tapping into AI technologies. This approach raises questions about the impact of AI on political discourse and public perception, especially amidst growing concerns about misinformation and authenticity online.  [Read More](https://www.npr.org/2024/08/30/nx-s1-5087913/donald-trump-artificial-intelligence-memes-deepfakes-taylor-swift)

<hr>

<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="150" align="left" style="padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px" />

According to Gartner, nearly one-third of all generative AI projects are predicted to be abandoned within the next few years. This statistic reflects the challenges organizations face when implementing such innovative technologies. Factors for abandonment include high costs, lack of expertise, and incomplete strategies. As companies navigate this evolving field, understanding these hurdles is essential for future success in AI endeavors. [Read More](https://www.zdnet.com/article/a-third-of-all-gen-ai-projects-will-be-abandoned-says-gartner/)

<hr>

<img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="150" align="left" style="padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px" />

Researchers at the University of Toronto have made significant strides in developing a new electrolyzer catalyst through artificial intelligence. This catalyst could enhance the efficiency of electrolysis in green hydrogen production, paving the way for more sustainable energy solutions. By integrating AI into the research process, they are accelerating innovation that could have a transformative impact on clean energy technologies and climate change mitigation.  [Read More](https://www.h2-view.com/story/university-of-toronto-uses-ai-to-discover-new-electrolyser-catalyst/2114334.article/)
